The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 26 November is 8,853 (1,024.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 21 November, there were 863 new confirmed cases (99.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 November, there were 1,076 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 20% (213 fewer cases).
